        "text": "Hi all! I've been lurking for a while (and have met some of you on donut calls). My name's Mike, and I make programming languages and tools. I got started early on with <https:\/\/julialang.org\/|Julia> and built a bunch of tools for <https:\/\/junolab.org\/|interactive development> and <https:\/\/github.com\/FluxML\/Zygote.jl|machine learning>. I'm proudest of <https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Flux_(machine-learning_framework)|Flux>, which influenced TensorFlow 2 and has been used for <https:\/\/mikeinnes.io\/posts\/flux\/|lots of cool research>. Nowadays I'm working on a little project called <https:\/\/github.com\/Unkindnesses\/raven|Raven>, which I'm pitching as a better way to use WebAssembly and as an <https:\/\/github.com\/Unkindnesses\/raven-js-template|escape hatch from JS>. I'm excited for what we can do by making powerful interactive languages accessible everywhere (<https:\/\/mikeinnes.io\/posts\/raven-tour\/|explorable explanations>? figma for code?), and resonate with ideas like malleable computing. It's early days but I think there's a lot of potential in those areas.\n\nI'll keep it short, but I'm more than happy to talk more, and to hear about any overlapping work :D I'd like to participate in more of the meetups in future too (sadly didn't see the last one in time). Glad this place exists!",
